title: Page from Ackermann's Repository
medium:
Medium: paper, cotton, silk
Technique: printed and glazed plain weave; plain weave with warp floats that form a diagonal rib pattern; printed plain weave
description: Single printed page from Ackermann's Repository No. XV, March, 1810. Three textile samples are pasted on the center of the page. The largest is a printed and glazed cotton in blue, green and black. The other two samples are an off-white silk with diagonal ribbing, and cotton printed with a dark and light brown abstract design.
name: Page from Ackermann's Repository
